The paper deals with the problem of set similarity joins, which is a common task in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses techniques for transferring the verification phase to the GPU, which involves data serialization, thread management, and set comparison. These topics are related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper presents experimental results that demonstrate significant speed-ups, which could be of interest to researchers in cs.PL (Programming Languages).
